				<name type="primary" sortindex="5" value="The hand that feeds, the hand that beats" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>The Hand That Feeds, The Hand That Beats.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Gods want power&amp;#10;... they'll do whatever it takes to get it...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In a world of faith, or better: a world of faiths, different followers worship different Gods.&amp;#10;The more faith and followers, the stronger a God is.&amp;#10;So they play their game of power and strength and sometimes just use the followers as playing pieces...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In The Hand that FEEDS, the Hand that BEATS, players represent a God and His followers. The priest of your faith&amp;#10;may call a creature that scoops up the whole village and moves them around the board. The followers can then be used&amp;#10;to acquire resources with which they build obilisks or the temple or a part of  one of the Gods' wonders: The Great Canal, The pyramid or the Mighty Colossus.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Three conditions trigger the game end:&amp;#10;1] If all three of the Gods' wonders are finished at the end of a round, the game ends.&amp;#10;2] If the creature-deck runs  out, the round is played to the end, after which the game ends.&amp;#10;3] After ten rounds, the game ends.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players try  to score the most victory points (VPs).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     If they build or convert obelisks or the temple they immediately score VPs.&amp;#10;     If they build parts of the Gods' wonders, they can score VPs every round.&amp;#10;     If they control the obelisk in the oasis, they score VPs if other players use the oasis.&amp;#10;     Some of the actions, miracles and disasters will earn a player VPs.&amp;#10;     Lastly, and most importantly, the most popular faith will be elected to feed all the players and receives VPs equal to the popularity of the faith.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
